headline.main: JERSEY SUSPENDS MEDICAID CHEATS; Alleges 10 Suppliers Filed False Payment Claims

byline.original: Special to The New York Times

docs.abstract: NJ Atty Gen Kugler says that Kendall Park Pharmacy, S Brunswick, NJ, has been convicted of allegedly filing false Medicaid claims and fined $50, NJ Munic Ct; Insts and Agencies Dept dir Kott says that A Kovnat, trading as Larkar Pharmacy (NJ), has been given 16-day suspension after allegedly abusing Medicaid program
docs.lead_paragraph: TRENTON, Dec. 4 -- State Attorney General George F. Kugler Jr. said today that some suppliers of medical services under New Jersey's Medicaid program had been filing false reimbursement claims.
docs.snippet: TRENTON, Dec. 4 -- State Attorney General George F. Kugler Jr. said today that some suppliers of medical services under New Jersey's Medicaid program had been filing false reimbursement claims.
